{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "These methods are all based on (1.1) -the equivalence to probability flow -to simulate the time evolution of Fokker-Planck solutions.",
    "[30] runs a large number of interacting deterministic particles where the gradient-log-density (score) function is approximated in the reproducing kernel Hilbert space (RKHS).",
    "[34,33] formulated a fixed-point problem for the self-consistency of the probability flow for the Fokker-Planck equation, but the optimization for the diffusion score function is based on the adjoint method which is in general slow and challenging to implement.",
    "The scorebased transport modeling in [4] is to march the flow sequentially in time with the forward Euler scheme.",
    "[29] extends this method to McKean-Vlasov SDEs with the assumption of bounded interaction potential."
  ],
